                            <comment id="17952457" author="garydgregory" created="Sun, 18 May 2025 15:52:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that the test as provided doesn&apos;t compile in the project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There&apos;s slop in the text.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use JUnit 5, not 4.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In addition:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The class name does not follow conventions: It should start with a capital letter and use camel case, not underscores.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use assertThrows(), not a custom try-catch block&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Please use a human filter before submitting machine-generated stuff.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition, you should see that the current behavior is expected, as shown in our unit tests. I&apos;ve clarified the Javadoc. Please verify if the text clears it up for you.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
